+    specfun::Status status = specfun::aswfa(x, int_m, int_n, c, kd, cv, &s1f, &s1d);","path":"scipy/special/xsf/sphd_wave.h","commit_id":"791b0938dffab2f3c121a009d8df84aab4812732","original_commit_id":"791b0938dffab2f3c121a009d8df84aab4812732","user":{"login":"WarrenWeckesser","id":321463,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTQ2Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/321463?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser","html_url":"https://github.com/WarrenWeckesser","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"Yes, that is definitely possible.  We could modify the functions in `specfun.h` to require preallocated work arrays.  This wouldn't be an immediate benefit, however, because *this* function (`prolate_aswfa_nocv()`) is still called for every set of scalar inputs, so the same repeated alloc and free is still happening.  To minimize memory allocations, a modification to the ufunc generation infrastructure is needed, so that the memory is allocated before entering the ufunc loop and freed after the loop.  To be specific, the loop that I'm talking about is one of

https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/bc0d3271b1243d9c0b3d05f3c2ac67fe4c5eb685/scipy/special/xsf/numpy.h#L819-L838

or

https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/bc0d3271b1243d9c0b3d05f3c2ac67fe4c5eb685/scipy/special/xsf/numpy.h#L785-L805

For this example, the `func` that is called in each iteration of the for-loop is `prolate_aswfa_nocv()`.  To minimize the repeated alloc/free, the allocation would need to happen before the for-loop is entered, and the free after the loop is exited.

(This wouldn't eliminate all repeated alloc/free, because when the inputs to the ufunc are higher-dimensional arrays, `loop()` itself is called multiple times by the NumPy ufunc looping machinery.)

This only works if the size of the required work array does not depend on the input values, which is not true for all the functions that do heap allocations.  When the size depends on the value, it might be necessary to do an initial pass over the data that was passed to `loop()` to find the worst case, and allocate that much before entering the main loop.  Or maybe something more clever is possible.

@izaid might have some ideas on how to cleanly incorporate some way of doing this in the C++ code.  Maybe something like pre- and post-loop functions that can be provided in the call that generates a ufunc?  It will need some way to ensure that the arrays that are generated in the pre-loop can be passed to the core function.  Or, perhaps a completely different approach would be that some ufuncs are generated from an explicitly implemented loop function (instead of just the scalar function); then we could do whatever is necessary before and after the loop.

Without such a modification to the ufunc generation code, there is no real benefit to moving the allocation up one level of function call.  Moving the allocation out of the function where it is needed  requires making implementation details of `aswfa()` (for example) available outside the function, which--in general--is something we would like to avoid.  But we definitely want to avoid the repeated alloc/free, so the change is worthwhile, if we anticipate that the required changes to the ufunc generation infrastructure will eventually be made.","created_at":"2024-12-16T19:19:23Z","updated_at":"2024-12-16T19:19:23Z","html_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080#discussion_r1887371438","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/22080","author_association":"MEMBER","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/comments/1887371438"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080#discussion_r1887371438"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/22080"}},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/comments/1887371438/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"start_line":null,"original_start_line":null,"start_side":null,"line":71,"original_line":71,"side":"RIGHT","in_reply_to_id":1887199125,"original_position":30,"position":30,"subject_type":"line"},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/22080","id":2235233019,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABZIoc6FOvL7","html_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080","diff_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/issues/22080","number":22080,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"WIP: special: Fix unchecked memory allocation in `aswfa()`","user":{"login":"WarrenWeckesser","id":321463,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTQ2Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/321463?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser","html_url":"https://github.com/WarrenWeckesser","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"This is a proof-of-concept for fixing https://github.com/scipy/scipy/issues/21417.

Only one of the functions ([`aswfa()`](https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/aba0dc1d1dc8cd060f0041caf8f8c7809c74f225/scipy/special/xsf/specfun/specfun.h#L126)) with unchecked calls of `calloc()` is fixed.  If this looks like a reasonable approach, the same pattern can be used to fix all the other unchecked allocations in `specfun.h`.

Summary of the changes:

* Add another SF error code, "SF_ERROR_NOMEM", that is used by ufuncs that require internally allocated memory.  Just like the other possible errors, how this error is handled can be queried and set using `geterr()` and `seterr()`.  Unlike the other error conditions, the default behavior is to raise an exception if a memory allocation fails.

* Modify the function `aswfa()` in `specfun.h` to return a status code that indicates when a memory allocation failed.

* Modify the functions `prolate_aswfa_nocv()`, `oblate_aswfa_nocv()`, `prolate_aswfa()` and `oblate_aswfa()`  in `sphd_wave.h` to check the return value of `aswfa()`, and set the error state and return values appropriately if `aswfa()` returns `NoMemory`.

Ping @izaid, @ilayn, @steppi.

