https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/bc0d3271b1243d9c0b3d05f3c2ac67fe4c5eb685/scipy/special/_special_ufuncs.cpp#L793-L796","created_at":"2024-12-16T19:56:09Z","updated_at":"2024-12-16T19:56:09Z","html_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080#discussion_r1887510739","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/22080","author_association":"MEMBER","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/comments/1887510739"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080#discussion_r1887510739"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/22080"}},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/comments/1887510739/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"start_line":null,"original_start_line":null,"start_side":null,"line":71,"original_line":71,"side":"RIGHT","in_reply_to_id":1887199125,"original_position":30,"position":30,"subject_type":"line"},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/pulls/22080","id":2235233019,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABZIoc6FOvL7","html_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080","diff_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/pull/22080.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/issues/22080","number":22080,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"WIP: special: Fix unchecked memory allocation in `aswfa()`","user":{"login":"WarrenWeckesser","id":321463,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTQ2Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/321463?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser","html_url":"https://github.com/WarrenWeckesser","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"This is a proof-of-concept for fixing https://github.com/scipy/scipy/issues/21417.

Only one of the functions ([`aswfa()`](https://github.com/scipy/scipy/blob/aba0dc1d1dc8cd060f0041caf8f8c7809c74f225/scipy/special/xsf/specfun/specfun.h#L126)) with unchecked calls of `calloc()` is fixed.  If this looks like a reasonable approach, the same pattern can be used to fix all the other unchecked allocations in `specfun.h`.

Summary of the changes:

* Add another SF error code, "SF_ERROR_NOMEM", that is used by ufuncs that require internally allocated memory.  Just like the other possible errors, how this error is handled can be queried and set using `geterr()` and `seterr()`.  Unlike the other error conditions, the default behavior is to raise an exception if a memory allocation fails.

* Modify the function `aswfa()` in `specfun.h` to return a status code that indicates when a memory allocation failed.

* Modify the functions `prolate_aswfa_nocv()`, `oblate_aswfa_nocv()`, `prolate_aswfa()` and `oblate_aswfa()`  in `sphd_wave.h` to check the return value of `aswfa()`, and set the error state and return values appropriately if `aswfa()` returns `NoMemory`.

Ping @izaid, @ilayn, @steppi.

