ments":9,"created_at":"2024-08-16T08:27:53Z","updated_at":"2024-08-18T13:50:09Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.

During discussion of gh-21370, it is found that a function that computes `(1+x)**y` accurately would be helpful for accurately computing the quantile function of Tukey lambda distribution.

### Describe the solution you'd like.

Add a function `scipy.special.pow1p(x, y)`, where $x \ge -1$ and $y \in \mathbb{R}$. The function shall return $(1+x)^y$ evaluated accurately.

### Describe alternatives you've considered.

Possible formulas to evaluate $(1+x)^y$ include `pow(1+x,y)` and `exp(y*log1p(x))`. But neither formula seems to be super accurate for `x` close to (and greater than) `-0.5` and large `y`; the relative error seems to exceed `1e-14`.

### Additional context (e.g. screenshots, GIFs)

IEEE-754 defines a similar function, `compound`, but its domain is restricted to integer `y`. I think it will be useful to support real `y`.

Doing a quick search of `pow1p` shows that R [introduced this function](https://stat.ethz.ch/pipermail/r-announce/2024/000701.html) in April, 2024. On other occasions, such a function is mentioned in [boost](https://www.boost.org/doc/libs/1_86_0/boost/math/special_functions/legendre.hpp) and [Julia](https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/6148).","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/issues/21404/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/issues/21404/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/issues/comments/2295270882","html_url":"https://github.com/scipy/scipy/issues/21404#issuecomment-2295270882","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/scipy/scipy/issues/21404","id":2295270882,"node_id":"IC_kwDOABZIoc6Izw3i","user":{"login":"WarrenWeckesser","id":321463,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMyMTQ2Mw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/321463?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser","html_url":"https://github.com/WarrenWeckesser","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/WarrenWeckesser/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-08-18T13:50:08Z","updated_at":"2024-08